VALUES('DEVX-17', 'Signature packs are not automatically triggering for Test hotel 1 in Marriott SM', 'For Test hotel 1 looks like the signature pack is not triggering automatically.We noticed this for 1/18 signature pack and when we trigger the pack (Signature mandatory style), we are receiving the following AOC“"Level: ":"WARN","Application: ":"SIGNATURE-TRIGGER","Environment: ":"prod","Message: ":"TRIGGER_CANCELLED","Reason: ":"Trigger cancel due to missing reports","Group: ":"ABC Hospitality","Hotel: ":"Test Hotel 1","Business Date: ":"2026-01-18","Type: ":"MANUAL","Scheduled As: ":"MANDATORY","Back days: ":0,"By: ":testuser@gmail.com","LogId: ":"aaabbb111-2345-6789-0123-ccc741eee852","Following report are missing or not in PDF format: ":"Report 1"“ But the “Report 1“ report is not a signature required report anymore.In Marriott SM, this report is listed as a signature-required report and also has a signature deactivation date.We configured the report this way because the client requested that the report appear as a non-signature report starting from 2025-01-29. When the report was originally created, it was first set up as a signature-required report.Normally, to make a report non-signature starting from a specific date, we disable the signature-mandatory toggle and add a signature deactivation date. This ensures that the report is treated as a non-signature report from the specified deactivation date onward.', NULL, 'To Do', 'Medium', 'Bug', 'Wiraj Gunasinghe', 'Portia Waduarachchi', '{}', '{}', '2026-03-26 11:44:17.322', NULL, '2026-03-26 14:02:05.182', '[{"id": "10006", "body": "Event processor app is receiving a signature enabled report, but it is recording a signature disabled Date report as a signature report. Therefore, it is not triggered automatically.", "author": "Portia Waduarachchi", "created": "2026-03-26T11:45:33.114+0530", "updated": "2026-03-26T11:45:33.114+0530"}]'::jsonb, '{"id": "10016", "key": "DEVX-17", "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/issue/10016", "expand": "renderedFields,names,schema,operations,editmeta,changelog,versionedRepresentations", "fields": {"labels": [], "status": {"id": "10000", "name": "To Do", "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/status/10000", "iconUrl": "https://nwnhemantha.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png", "description": "", "statusCategory": {"id": 2, "key": "new", "name": "To Do", "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/statuscategory/2", "colorName": "blue-gray"}}, "comment": {"self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/issue/10016/comment", "total": 1, "startAt": 0, "comments": [{"id": "10006", "body": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "Event processor app is receiving a ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "signature enabled", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "strong"}]}, {"text": " report, but it is recording a ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "signature disabled Date ", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "strong"}]}, {"text": "report as a signature report. Therefore, it is not triggered automatically.", "type": "text"}]}], "version": 1}, "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/issue/10016/comment/10006", "author": {"self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/user?accountId=611cda33c6021e0069460313", "active": true, "timeZone": "Asia/Colombo", "accountId": "611cda33c6021e0069460313", "avatarUrls": {"16x16": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5a0fc7c165252fc8a1beed35a2c82de2?d=https%3A%2F%2Favatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net%2Finitials%2FPW-4.png", "24x24": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5a0fc7c165252fc8a1beed35a2c82de2?d=https%3A%2F%2Favatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net%2Fi