VALUES('DEVX-23', 'Hotel QC ID Not Populating — Blocking Creation of 2 New TestHMG''s Hotels', 'I am unable to successfully create the following properties in System Manager for DigiAudit due to the Hotel QC ID not populating: Test Hotel 1 - TH1Test Hotel 2 - TH2 The two properties appear to be saved in System Manager, when searching under Hotels > View. However, the fields that I originally filled out - Primary Project, Time Zone, Hotel Status - that information is removed. *To note, these two properties also are set up in Rec, the hotels were originally created in CRM before switching to System Manager for Rec onboardings. ', NULL, 'To Do', 'Medium', 'Bug', 'Asiri Indatissa', 'Portia Waduarachchi', '{}', '{}', '2026-03-26 15:30:49.723', NULL, '2026-03-26 15:50:55.847', '[{"id": "10015", "body": "An error message appears that says Hotel code already exists", "author": "Portia Waduarachchi", "created": "2026-03-26T15:32:34.238+0530", "updated": "2026-03-26T15:32:34.238+0530"}, {"id": "10016", "body": "Based on the data TH1, TH2 was created in 2022-07. It seems this didn’t migrate properly.Snowflake has those 2 hotel codes.TH1 → ID (0001)TH2 → ID (0002)But cannot see mapping ID under MongoDB record (above IDs should be listed as hotel_id in the mongo collection).Should alter the mongo collection for the above two hotels.", "author": "Portia Waduarachchi", "created": "2026-03-26T15:43:56.519+0530", "updated": "2026-03-26T15:43:56.519+0530"}, {"id": "10017", "body": "The changes are completed on Mongo DB", "author": "Portia Waduarachchi", "created": "2026-03-26T15:44:59.619+0530", "updated": "2026-03-26T15:44:59.619+0530"}, {"id": "10018", "body": "It seems that the qc_hotel_id is not created. This one was created in QC DB(SQL Server). We need to check whether the backend has access to QC DB. DevOps Can you check in the Hotels table under QC DB forQCHotelName : Test Hotel 2", "author": "Portia Waduarachchi", "created": "2026-03-26T15:49:04.545+0530", "updated": "2026-03-26T15:49:04.545+0530"}, {"id": "10019", "body": "We found that this issue occurred when trying to update the QC database on the Signature_time table. We added a default value to the columns and tested it with the QA team. Now, the QC ID is populating correctly on the PS side.", "author": "Portia Waduarachchi", "created": "2026-03-26T15:50:55.847+0530", "updated": "2026-03-26T15:50:55.847+0530"}]'::jsonb, '{"id": "10022", "key": "DEVX-23", "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/issue/10022", "expand": "renderedFields,names,schema,operations,editmeta,changelog,versionedRepresentations", "fields": {"labels": [], "status": {"id": "10000", "name": "To Do", "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/status/10000", "iconUrl": "https://nwnhemantha.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png", "description": "", "statusCategory": {"id": 2, "key": "new", "name": "To Do", "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/statuscategory/2", "colorName": "blue-gray"}}, "comment": {"self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/issue/10022/comment", "total": 5, "startAt": 0, "comments": [{"id": "10015", "body": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "An error message appears that says Hotel code already exists", "type": "text"}]}], "version": 1}, "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/issue/10022/comment/10015", "author": {"self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/6a02dde6-47b8-4c00-a42c-3bd078e9c043/rest/api/3/user?accountId=611cda33c6021e0069460313", "active": true, "timeZone": "Asia/Colombo", "accountId": "611cda33c6021e0069460313", "avatarUrls": {"16x16": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5a0fc7c165252fc8a1beed35a2c82de2?d=https%3A%2F%2Favatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net%2Fini